Distribution of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia muriculata" order="Myrtales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="muriculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Conostegia muriculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia muriculata" order="Myrtales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="muriculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Conostegia muriculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a distinctive species recognized by being overall glabrous, pendant inflorescence, purple petals and muriculate seeds. Unfortunately the phylogenetic placement of this species remains unknown. Because of its small flower buds and being almost totally glabrous, it likely belongs in the 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia montana" order="Myrtales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Conostegia montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex in section 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Conostegia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Conostegia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As in all species in section 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Conostegia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Conostegia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the style is short (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 93" captionStartId="F93" captionText="Figure 93. Conostegia muriculata. A Inflorescence B Lateral view of flower C Frontal view of flower. Photographs by Laurencio Martinez." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure93" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96451" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">93</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
mentions the fact that several specimen labels point to an understory habitat and suggests it is probably a shade tolerant species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
